- Context: This page contains information about SSOW responsibilities and a step-by-step overview of the audit and review process.
- Text: SSOW Responsibilities
SSoW must ensure that roles and responsibilities are assigned for the effective management
of hazards and control measures. Typical role responsibilities include:
•
SSoW Owner: Accountable for the safe system of work
•
SSoW Responsible Person: Responsible for managing the SSoW throughout its lifecycle
•
Supervisors: Responsible for overseeing safe execution of work
•
Workers: Responsible for safe execution of work
A Step-By-Step Overview of the Audit & Review Process
•
Understand the Scope and Boundaries of the SSoW
•
•
Gather Relevant Documentation
•
•
Carry out the Audit
•
•
Present and Discuss Findings
•
•
Agree and Implement Actions
•
•
Document and Close Out
•
Identify Relevant Legislation and Good Practice
Conduct a Gap Analysis Against Standards
